It's weird when you realize you no longer have friends you can call at 1:30am. Few people are even on aim. What happened to everyone?

Posted via LiveJournal.app.

so this morning betty woke up really early and was running frantically around the house. I knew she was on some sort of mission but i went to bed at 3 and it was 8 so there was no way i was going to wake up and figure out what it was. Erik got up before i did and went to take a shower and in the bathtub found out what betty's mission of the morning was....
someone please explain this to me

erik and i got home from dana's the other day to find that betty had escaped from the kitchen baby gates once again.  usually when we get home there might be a bit of pee on the floor and maybe a few things knocked off the couch... this time she managed to shatter a glass across the living room and somehow make my computer talk.  i have no clue how the talking happened and if anyone gets bored and wants to find out the mac keyboard short cut for turning the speaking feature on i would love to know how it happened.  poor dog is getting crazier by the day
we drove by the flash waiting at a bus stop....  it was kind of sad he couldn't just run on home. today we get to sit in a free clinic to get erik's foot fixed... fun times.
sometimes i think i am just not cut out of happiness...
when you ask soeone "should i stay" and they say "no" you know you are failing in life
i have hit an alltime low, i am playing poker on facebook and talkig to the people on there.....

my horoscope can scare me...

It's not easy to open your heart before you are clear about what you want. Nevertheless, your courage will be rewarded if you simply share your current thoughts and feelings without trying to get anyone else to cure your ambiguity. The beauty in this is that your openness to the present moment can create a special magic that is not available if you begin with a specific agenda.
this is  my goodbye to you.  it took some time but i can finally say goodbye.  i still and always will love you.

it is amazing how easy it is for certain people to find better things to do when they said they would do something for you.  i wish i kept score or held grudges because this would be a nice thing to remember next time i am needed by said person.

in other news.. i am going to denver tomorrow which will rock.  jessica is coming out and so is matt and we will have so much fun i might even forget about pooheads who cant make time for me.  the convention looks amazing, i was looking at the line up today and it hink it will be great. 

 oh and the glorytellers (2 members from karate, though not the one i long to see) will be playing in denver on sat night so i might get to see them.  and the 3rd karate member better get his butt back to the states soon so i can see him to because i miss him and his face.

ok back to finishing packing and such... i miss all of you.

or mornings when 4am hits and i still cannot sleep i start thinking way to much.  so i turn to you my dear internet friend, here for me to talk to no matter what hour of the night.  i guess i should crawl in bed with the little lady who is there already and hope the dogs don't wake me up at 7am.  

i spent the night cleaning up vomit from all over my bedroom, maybe that is why i cant sleep, the smell of puke seeping out of my floor.  note to self: don't get friends too drunk.

my myspace got totally hacked where i canot even access it.  damn it. i have to have them deltate it but that is troublesome in the way the say to do it.  oh well.  so e-mail me instead of myspacing me and i will set up another one at some point.
how is it possible that you can do this to me.

everything has been so crazy lately with friends and changes in life (i am done with these changes).  i have decided once again girls are bad news as i ended up int he middle of some unwanted drama that i was not at all involved in but kinda led to andria saying she doesnt think she can hang out with me because i am friends with someone the drama did involve.   pretty lame to loose one of my best friends over something neither of us were involved in but she got dragged into and i guess i did too somehow by the way it turned out.  ahhh.

as of the beginning of november i will be adopting another dog from a friend who cant take care of it anymore.  two ilttle black and white fur balls.

ava will be moving out at the end of november and chris and betty will be moving in on december 1st so we will have 3 dogs and 2 people which will rule!  doggy fun for all.

for now i need to get back to cleaning my room.

i found the secret to happiness, or at elast something to make the days  little easier.

andria's amazing home made mac and cheese reheated from last night and a budweiser.

everything might just be ok now

horoscopes can be a bit weird at time.....

"It may feel like a losing battle now as you attempt to hold on to your fading optimism, but it may be the best thing you can do. If you start questioning your long-term goals, you could spiral down into despair -- and this won't lead to anything productive. Be aware of what's going on, but don't just look at the dark side. There is a silver lining to the rain cloud."

Star Wars Horoscope for Sagittarius
You are superbly wise and have been known to spread your wisdom widely. You are impatient and pushy when people take your teachings too lightly. And your philosophical side always peeks through. Star wars character you are most like: Yoda
What Is Your Star Wars Horoscope?

if anyone can tell me where the headline for this is from i will love you forever.  anyways.  i need to stop staying up till 5am and later i think it is going to end up catching up with me.  i guess i do need to have some fun in my life though so for now, party on!
tonight i was invited to join a group of people who are going to be playing d and d.  i am so fucking excited, now i just need to learn how to play magic....

as i was leaving 101 cafe today i saw one of the hobbits from lord of the rings (who is also on lost).  but anyways as i saw him i realized he as staring at my tits.  oh yeah i got cruised by a hobbit.  fuck yeah, i think i just made some super dork points with that one.

woke up
went to t.o. and saw jesse
did laundry
ran errands
dropped jesse off (it was great to see you)
went to the observatory with jeff grube and friends
came home
picked up some large red stripes
parked the car
got in the backseat and drank with jeff
walked down to jumbos
watched pretty girls in their underwear
came home
slept



twas a pretty good day
i need to dance more often.

ava is starting to move her stuff in today, it will be nice having her around.  She came over last night and we just sat in the living room floor talking.  it is so weird that my life has changed so much in the past 3 months and i would have never guessed this is where it would all end up.  i guess i have to make the best of this unwanted new beginning and keep looking forward in hopes i will figure this all out.  some amazing friends have made things a bit easier but it still hurts.  now i am going to shower and go to yoga and maybe even watch a soccer game if i can figure out when it is on.
it is weird when you realize that certain people who have been in your life are no longer there.  well not weird but sad that people can move in and out of your life so eaisily.

so we went on a whirlwind trip to s.f. this weekend (we = me, katie and chris bassett)  this is how it went

i got a call friday morn that i didnt have to go to work so we bumped up the trip to leave at 1ish, i went to breakfast with a friend and got home too late to remember to pack much of anything (good thing i was stayng with jessica)  we got on the road and i noticed there was a wobble in the car but katie said it jst wa s like that.  after i made chris drive because i was tired the tire tread flew off and we had to put on the spare and jessica found us a wallmart to get the thing fixed at.  after about an hour in wall mart we were back on the road and made it to jessica's safe and sound.

sat we woke up late and ran around the city and made katie lay on a table and get some needles in her side then we came home and watched snakes on a plane (it mother-fuckin rules)

today we woke up ate bagels went to visit jessica at work, went on a long walk, ate a great dinner and drove home.  i totally needed this weekend and i had a great time, hopefully i will be able to do it again soon.

jessica you rule!

Your Power Element is Earth
Your power color: yellow Your energy: balancing Your season: changing of seasons Dedicated and responsible, you are a rock to your friends. You are skilled at working out even the most difficult problems. Low key and calm, you are happiest when you are around loved ones. Ambitious and goal oriented, you have long term plans to be successful.
What's Your Power Element?
i had almost forgotten how much hangovers suck but i reminded myself today.  i feel like shit, come take care of me.
going to s.f. next weekend.  yay for jessica and micah and alcohol and katie.
here i am again crying and alone.

i just woke up... it is 6am and i am wide awake.  i hate how i wake up with so much on my mind i cannot sleep at all.  oh well i will go lay in bed for another few hours before i have to wake up, wish me luck on falling asleep.
it's weird to realize how alone you really are.

i have been moving stuff around in my apartment for 4 hours now.  how can one person have crap worth 4 hours of moving room to room.  someone save me.

i saw spiderman at 12:20 last night which ruled but i got home at 3:20 so just make sure when you see it you know it is super good and long.  aldo for all of you sad emo kids out there the black suit spiderman acquires in this movie turns him into connor oberst.  it rules.

i saw silent hill last night which is one of he most amazing nonsense horror films to ever be made.  if anyone is into yelling at the the t.v. for 2 hours to a movie that i still dont fully understand it is fully worth it.  but i am a sucker for bad scary movies.

so this past week has been spent on the right coast of the united states.  erica i miss you already and can't wait till you are back home to go hiking with and enjoy long nights watching movies and drinking wine.  after a short stay in new york that ended waiting for a bus in a line a bit too close to a line full of people waiting to audition for "so you think you can dance" 

we headed to our nations capital to visit fromar and ziska.  the first night there me and ziska had a good amount of alcohol and we all headed out dancing... they told me we called ryan and i remember the phone being to my ear but could not tell you what either of us said.  the rest of the trip was a bit more mellow filled with board games and walks through the streets and museums.  

now i am home and though i had a ton of fun and glad to be home.  but hopefully i will get to see omar and ziska in juneish and erica in a few weeks.  now ryan just needs to get his ass back out here and everything will be perfect!
